<div class="privacy-section pt-100 pb-100">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="privacy-text">
            <h2>Guide To Applying</h2>

            <p>
                Before you start the application process, you will be asked to log in or register. You will be able to save your progress and review all your answers before you submit them. A <a href="/static/doaj/docs/2021-02-17-DOAJQuestions.pdf">PDF version of the application form</a> is available for reference only.
            </p>
            <h2>Basic criteria for inclusion</h2>
            <h3>The type of journal that can apply</h3>
            <p>Open access journals published in any language may apply.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Newly launched journals
                    <ul>
                        <li>Before applying to Axiomindexing, a new journal must demonstrate a publishing history of more than one year, or have published at least 10 articles.</li>
                        <li>This is in addition to the standard requirement to publish a minimum of 5 research articles per year.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    The journal must be actively publishing scholarly research
                    <ul>
                        <li>All research subject areas are accepted</li>
                        <li>Should publish at least 5 research articles per year</li>
                        <li>The primary target audience should be researchers or practitioners</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <hr>
            <h3 id="the-type-of-open-access">The type of open access</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>The journal must have its own dedicated URL and homepage that is accessible from any location</li>
                <li>The website must be clear and easy to navigate</li>
                <li>The journal should adhere to the guidelines described in the Principles of Transparency and Best Practice in Scholarly Publishing</li>
                <li>
                    Each article must be available as an individual, full-text article
                    <ul>
                        <li>one unique URL per article</li>
                        <li>HTML or PDF, as a minimum</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Journals that include intrusive advertising will not be accepted. See best practice <a href="https://www.doaj.org/apply/transparency" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">recommendations</a> for advertising. </li>
                <li>Axiomindexing does not approve of the use of Impact Factors. However, we acknowledge that the only official Impact Factor is that created by Clarivate. Journals must not display Impact Factors/similar rankings from any other service</li>
                <li>The website does not need to be in English. If the site is available in multiple languages the information provided must be the same in all languages.</li>
            </ul>

            <p>The following information must be available online, and easily accessible from the journal homepage:</p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        Editorial board information
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Contact information for the editorial office
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Peer review process information
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Open access and copyright information
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Publication ethics and malpractice statement
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Author guidelines and submission process information
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Publication frequency and history of the journal
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Indexing and abstracting information
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Funding and sponsorship information, if applicable
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <h3 id="the-type-of-open-access">Submitting your application</h3>
            <p>
                Once you have ensured that your journal meets the basic criteria for inclusion, you can submit your application. You will be asked to provide information about your journal, including its title, ISSN, and publication frequency. You will also need to provide information about your editorial board, peer review process, and open access policies.
                Axiomindexing reserves the right to request additional information if necessary.

                After submitting your application, Axiomindexing will review your journal to ensure that it meets our inclusion criteria. The review process can take up to 4-6 weeks, and you will be notified of the outcome by email.
                If your journal is accepted for indexing, it will be added to the Axiomindexing database and become searchable by users around the world.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
